'''Rani Khedira''' ({{langx|ar|راني خضيرة}}; born 27 January 1994) is a professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[midfielder]] for {{German football updater|UnionBer}} club [[1. FC Union Berlin|Union Berlin]]. Born in Germany, he plays for the [[Tunisia national football team|Tunisia national team]].

==Club career==

===VfB Stuttgart===
Khedira started his youth career at TV Oeffingen before moving to [[VfB Stuttgart]] in 2005, a year before his older brother, [[Sami Khedira|Sami]], joined.<ref name="Khedira Stuttgart"/><ref name="Khedira Stuttgart2">{{cite web|url=http://www.vfb.de/de/vfb/aktuell/news-archiv/2013/297678--wir-sind-nicht-zufrieden-/|title="Wir sind nicht zufrieden"|publisher=VfB Stuttgart|language=German|date=16 December 2013|accessdate=26 June 2017|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170626190233/http://www.vfb.de/de/vfb/aktuell/news-archiv/2013/297678--wir-sind-nicht-zufrieden-/|archivedate=26 June 2017|url-status=live}}</ref> After progressing the ranks of Stuttgart Academy, he began to play for the U16 side by 2009.<ref>{{cite news|title=Sami KhediraIn BILD erklärt sein Vater den Nationalspieler|url=http://www.bild.de/sport/fussball/sein-vater-erklaert-in-bild-den-nationalspieler-9718158.bild.html|publisher=Bild.de|language=German|date=11 September 2009|accessdate=26 June 2017}}</ref> He signed a contract with the club, keeping him until 2013.<ref>{{cite news|title=Khedira-Bruder Rani spielt in StuttgartDie Super-Talente der Bundesliga|url=http://www.bild.de/sport/fussball/1-bundesliga/bild-stellt-die-supertalente-vor-25020116.bild.html|publisher=Bild.de|language=German|date=28 January 2012|accessdate=26 June 2017}}</ref> On 28 January 2012, Khedira had his debut for [[VfB Stuttgart II]] in the [[3. Liga]] against [[FC Rot-Weiß Erfurt]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Reichwein macht es doppelt|url=https://www.kicker.de/erfurt-gegen-vfb-ii-2012-liga-1146694/analyse|publisher=[[Kicker (magazine)|Kicker]]|language=German|date=28 January 2012|access-date=26 June 2017}}</ref> During his time at VfB Stuttgart's reserves, he scored once for the side, in a 4–0 win over [[SV Wacker Burghausen|Wacker Burghausen]] on 8 September 2013.<ref>{{cite news|title=VfB Stuttgart II besiegt Burghausen mit 4:0|url=http://www.bild.de/regional/stuttgart/vfb-stuttgart-ii-besiegt-burghausen-mit-40-32307468.bild.html|publisher=Bild.de|language=German|date=8 September 2013|accessdate=26 June 2017}}</ref>

On 23 October 2012, Khedira was promoted to the first team of VfB Stuttgart.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.vfb.de/de/aktuell/meldungen/news/2012/mamadou-bah-im-u23-kader-des-vfb-stuttgart/page/4872-0-3-1351006887.html|title=Rani Khedira rückt auf|work=[[VfB Stuttgart]]|accessdate=23 October 2012|date=23 October 2012|language=German|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161226085643/http://www.vfb.de/de/aktuell/meldungen/news/2012/mamadou-bah-im-u23-kader-des-vfb-stuttgart/page/4872-0-3-1351006887.html|archivedate=26 December 2016|url-status=dead}}</ref> He extended his contract with the club on 28 January 2013 until June 2015.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.vfb.de/en/aktuell/meldungen/news/2013/vertragsverlaengerung-rani-khedira-vfb-stuttgart/page/2061-1-1-1359388821.html|title=Khedira extends deal until 2015|work=vfb.de|publisher=[[VfB Stuttgart]]|date=28 January 2013|accessdate=28 January 2013|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160303235343/http://www.vfb.de/en/aktuell/meldungen/news/2013/vertragsverlaengerung-rani-khedira-vfb-stuttgart/page/2061-1-1-1359388821.html|archivedate=3 March 2016|url-status=dead}}</ref> However throughout the 2012–13 season, Khedira never made his first team appearances, as he appeared for most of the season as an unused substitute.<ref>{{cite news|title=Kommt Rani Khedira für Gentner nach?|url=https://www.kicker.de/kommt-khedira-fuer-gentner-nach-578001/artikel|publisher=[[Kicker (magazine)|Kicker]]|language=German|date=21 November 2012|access-date=26 June 2017}}</ref>

On 1 September 2013, Khedira made his [[Bundesliga]] debut for VfB Stuttgart in a 6–2 home victory against [[TSG 1899 Hoffenheim|1899 Hoffenheim]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Ibisevic macht das halbe Dutzend voll|url=https://www.kicker.de/stuttgart-gegen-hoffenheim-2013-bundesliga-1894903/analyse|publisher=[[Kicker (magazine)|Kicker]]|language=German|date=1 September 2013|access-date=26 June 2017}}</ref> On 7 December 2013, when he made his first start for Stuttgart, in a 4–2 win over [[Hannover 96]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Ibisevic macht das halbe Dutzend voll|url=https://www.kicker.de/stuttgart-gegen-hoffenheim-2013-bundesliga-1894903/analyse|publisher=[[Kicker (magazine)|Kicker]]|language=German|date=7 December 2013|access-date=26 June 2017}}</ref> From 29 January 2014 and 2 March 2014, he had a handful of starting his first team places.<ref>{{cite news|title=Schneider testet Bubi YalcinSechser-Sensation beim VfB|url=http://www.bild.de/sport/fussball/thomas-schneider/sechser-sensation-beim-vfb-34755560.bild.html|publisher=Bild.de|language=German|date=20 February 2014|accessdate=26 June 2017}}</ref> Although he lost his first team place later on, Khedira went on to make nine appearances for the club.

===RB Leipzig===

For the [[2014–15 2. Bundesliga|2014–15 season]], Khedira moved to [[RB Leipzig]], signing a three-year contract, keeping him until 2017.<ref>{{cite news|title=RB holt Khedira - und will auch Boyd|url=https://www.kicker.de/rb-holt-khedira---und-will-auch-boyd-606315/artikel|publisher=[[Kicker (magazine)|Kicker]]|language=German|date=26 June 2014|access-date=26 June 2017}}</ref> The move was reported to be undisclosed.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.vfb.de/en/aktuell/meldungen/news/2014/transfer-rani-khedira/page/3100-1-1-.html|title=Rani Khedira leaves VfB|work=vfb.de|publisher=[[VfB Stuttgart]]|date=17 June 2014|accessdate=17 June 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160303224434/http://www.vfb.de/en/aktuell/meldungen/news/2014/transfer-rani-khedira/page/3100-1-1-.html|archivedate=3 March 2016|url-status=live}}</ref> RB Leipzig had been keen on signing him since September 2013.<ref>{{cite news|title=Wann gibt es den ersten Gomez aus Leipzig?|url=http://www.bild.de/sport/fussball/rb-leipzig/ueber-aufstieg-und-talente-32367546.bild.html|publisher=Bild.de|language=German|date=13 September 2013|accessdate=26 June 2017}}</ref>

Khedira made his RB Leipzig debut in the opening game of the season, playing the whole game, in a 0–0 draw against [[VfR Aalen]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Leipzigs Pressing bringt keinen Erfolg|url=https://www.kicker.de/leipzig-gegen-aalen-2014-bundesliga-2407540/analyse|publisher=[[Kicker (magazine)|Kicker]]|language=German|date=2 August 2014|access-date=26 June 2017}}</ref> After making his RB Leipzig debut, he quickly established himself in the first team and played a key role for the club in his first season.<ref>{{cite news|title=In Leipzig spielt Khedira eine Rolle|url=https://www.kicker.de/in-leipzig-spielt-khedira-eine-rolle-620455/artikel|publisher=[[Kicker (magazine)|Kicker]]|language=German|date=4 February 2015|access-date=26 June 2017}}</ref> He also became a regular start player from the beginning of the season until he was suspended for one match against [[SV Sandhausen]] on 30 November 2014 having picked up five yellow cards this season.<ref>{{cite news|title=Zorniger: "Sandhausen ist eine Macht"|url=https://www.kicker.de/zorniger_sandhausen-ist-eine-macht-616401/artikel|publisher=[[Kicker (magazine)|Kicker]]|language=German|date=28 November 2014|access-date=26 June 2017}}</ref> However, in a 1–0 loss against [[FSV Frankfurt]] on 15 February 2015, he suffered a leg injury in the 69th minute and was substituted as a result.<ref>{{cite news|title=Roshi nutzt Coltortis Blackout|url=https://www.kicker.de/leipzig-gegen-fsv-frankfurt-2015-bundesliga-2407720/analyse|publisher=[[Kicker (magazine)|Kicker]]|language=German|date=15 February 2015|access-date=26 June 2017}}</ref> The injury kept him out of action for several weeks.<ref>{{cite news|title=Erneute Pause für Leipzigs Khedira|url=https://www.kicker.de/erneute-pause-fuer-leipzigs-khedira-622025/artikel|publisher=[[Kicker (magazine)|Kicker]]|language=German|date=27 February 2015|access-date=26 June 2017}}</ref> On 17 May 2015, he returned to the first team from injury, in a 2–1 loss against [[FC Ingolstadt 04|Ingolstadt]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Lex erlöst die Schanzer - Ingolstadt steigt auf|url=https://www.kicker.de/ingolstadt-gegen-leipzig-2015-bundesliga-2407825/analyse|publisher=[[Kicker (magazine)|Kicker]]|language=German|date=17 May 2015|access-date=26 June 2017}}</ref> In his first season at the club, Khedira went on to make 24 appearances in all competitions.

[[File:Rani khedira.jpg|thumb|right|upright|Khedira in 2012]]

In his second season at RB Leipzig, Khedira found himself in a competition for his position and this resulted in him sitting on the substitutes bench at the start of the season.<ref>{{cite news|title=Leipzigs Khedira soll ein Spezialist werden|url=https://www.kicker.de/leipzigs-khedira-soll-ein-spezialist-werden-642409/artikel|publisher=[[Kicker (magazine)|Kicker]]|language=German|date=7 January 2016|access-date=26 June 2017}}</ref> Later in the season, he was plagued by injuries.<ref>{{cite news|title=Rangnick fordert Balleroberungen - Khedira fällt aus|url=https://www.kicker.de/rangnick-fordert-balleroberungen---khedira-faellt-aus-636353/artikel|publisher=[[Kicker (magazine)|Kicker]]|language=German|date=2 October 2015|access-date=26 June 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Weinzierl in Leipzig aus dem Rennen - Khedira verletzt|url=https://www.kicker.de/weinzierl-in-leipzig-aus-dem-rennen---khedira-verletzt-648613/artikel|publisher=[[Kicker (magazine)|Kicker]]|language=German|date=2 April 2016|access-date=26 June 2017}}</ref> Nevertheless, he went on to make 16 appearances in all competitions, as RB Leipzig were promoted to the [[Bundesliga]].

Ahead of the 2016–17 season, Khedira's first team opportunities continued to be limited and remained on the substitute bench following new competitions and by November, he had not made his first appearance of the season.<ref>{{cite news|title=Leipzig-KhediraDer traurigste Stammplatz der Liga|url=http://www.bild.de/bild-plus/sport/fussball/rani-khedira/der-traurigste-stammplatz-der-liga-48574278.bild.html|publisher=Bild.de|language=German|date=2 November 2016|accessdate=27 June 2017|archive-url=http://web.archive.org/web/20161106234827/http://www.bild.de/bild-plus/sport/fussball/rani-khedira/der-traurigste-stammplatz-der-liga-48574278,view=conversionToLogin.bild.html|archive-date=2016-11-06}}</ref> On 25 November 2016, he made his first appearance of the 2016–17 season, coming on as a second-half substitute, in a 4–1 win over [[SC Freiburg|Freiburg]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Keitas Knaller gibt gleich die Richtung vor|url=https://www.kicker.de/freiburg-gegen-leipzig-2016-bundesliga-3317361/analyse|publisher=[[Kicker (magazine)|Kicker]]|language=German|date=25 November 2016|access-date=27 June 2017}}</ref> He went on to make ten appearances for the club this season. However, it was announced that Khedira was released by the club.<ref>{{cite news|title=Compper verlängert - Khedira sagt Adieu|url=https://www.kicker.de/compper-verlaengert---khedira-sagt-adieu-678553/artikel|publisher=[[Kicker (magazine)|Kicker]]|language=German|date=21 May 2017|access-date=27 June 2017}}</ref> He had previously been advised by his brother not to leave the club.<ref>{{cite news|title=FußballSami Khedira riet Bruder Rani von Leipzig-Weggang ab|url=http://www.bild.de/sport/aktuelles/fussball/sami-khedira-riet-bruder-rani-von-leipzigweggang-50655546.bild.html|publisher=Bild.de|language=German|date=1 March 2017|accessdate=27 June 2017}}</ref>

===FC Augsburg===
With his RB Leipzig contract expiring at the end of the 2016–17 season, Khedira joined fellow Bundesliga club [[FC Augsburg]] on 7 June 2017, signing a four-year contract.<ref>{{cite news|title=Augsburg angelt sich Rani Khedira|url=https://www.kicker.de/augsburg-angelt-sich-rani-khedira-679658/artikel|publisher=[[Kicker (magazine)|Kicker]]|language=German|date=7 June 2017|access-date=26 June 2017}}</ref>

===Union Berlin===
In April 2021, Khedira was announced to join [[1. FC Union Berlin|Union Berlin]] starting from the 2021–22 season.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.rbb24.de/sport/beitrag/2021/04/fussball-1-fc-union-berlin-rani-khedira-wechsel.html |title=Rani Khedira wechselt vom FC Augsburg zu Union Berlin |publisher=rbb24.de |language=de |date=26 April 2021 |access-date=27 May 2023 |archive-date=1 June 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230601150956/https://www.rbb24.de/sport/beitrag/2021/04/fussball-1-fc-union-berlin-rani-khedira-wechsel.html |url-status=dead }}</ref> On 19 March 2023, he scored his first goal at the club in a 2–0 win over [[Eintracht Frankfurt]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.fc-union-berlin.de/de/fussball/profis/spielplan/detail/-1-FC-Union-Berlin-Eintracht-Frankfurt-16624r/ |title=Union schlägt Frankfurt mit 2:0 |publisher=Union Berlin |language=de |date=19 March 2023 |access-date=27 May 2023 |archive-date=1 March 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240301112326/https://www.fc-union-berlin.de/de/fussball/profis/spielplan/detail/-1-FC-Union-Berlin-Eintracht-Frankfurt-16624r/ |url-status=dead }}</ref> On the final matchday of the 2022–23 season, he scored the only goal in a 1–0 victory over [[SV Werder Bremen|Werder Bremen]], to secure the fourth place for his club in the league and qualification to the next season's [[2023–24 UEFA Champions League|Champions League]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.sportschau.de/fussball/bundesliga/bundesliga-spielbericht-fc-union-berlin-werder-bremen-100.html |title=Khedira schießt Union in die Champions League |publisher=Sportschau |language=de |date=27 May 2023 |archive-url=http://web.archive.org/web/20230527170813/https://www.sportschau.de/fussball/bundesliga/bundesliga-spielbericht-fc-union-berlin-werder-bremen-100.html|archive-date=2023-05-27}}</ref>

==International career==
After being featured for [[Germany national youth football team|Germany U15]] and [[Germany national youth football team|Germany U16]], Khedira was featured for [[Germany national youth football team|Germany U17]] and played for Germany at the [[2011 FIFA U-17 World Cup]], where he played five times in the tournament.<ref>{{cite news|title=Freund benennt seinen WM-Kader|url=https://www.kicker.de/freund-benennt-seinen-wm-kader-553422/artikel|publisher=[[Kicker (magazine)|Kicker]]|language=German|date=3 June 2011|access-date=26 June 2017}}</ref> The following year, Khedira was called up [[Germany national youth football team|Germany U19]] and immediately made an impact when he scored on his debut, in a 3–0 win over France U19 on 14 November 2012.<ref>{{cite news|title=U 19 lässt Frankreich abblitzen|url=https://www.kicker.de/u-19-laesst-frankreich-abblitzen-577725/artikel|publisher=[[Kicker (magazine)|Kicker]]|language=German|date=14 November 2012|access-date=27 June 2017}}</ref> He made another Germany U19 appearance on 25 March 2013, in a 2–0 win over Ukraine U19.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.vfb.de/de/vfb/aktuell/news-archiv/2013/293600-testspielsieg-fuer-dfb-u19/|title=Testspielsieg für DFB-U19|publisher=VfB Stuttgart|language=German|date=14 November 2012|accessdate=27 June 2017|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170627203506/http://www.vfb.de/de/vfb/aktuell/news-archiv/2013/293600-testspielsieg-fuer-dfb-u19/|archivedate=27 June 2017|url-status=live}}</ref>

Three years on, Khedira earned a call-up by [[Germany national under-21 football team|Germany U21]] in November 2014.<ref>{{cite news|title=Khediras Deutschland-Debüt platzt|url=https://www.kicker.de/zorniger_sandhausen-ist-eine-macht-616401/artikel|publisher=[[Kicker (magazine)|Kicker]]|language=German|date=12 November 2014|access-date=26 June 2017}}</ref> Through his father, he is eligible to play for [[Tunisia national football team|Tunisia]], but he rejected call-ups to the team from the Tunisian FA.<ref>{{cite news|title=Khedira: "Gab nie den Gedanken, für Tunesien zu spielen"|url=http://www.fussballtransfers.com/nachricht/nationalmannschaft-rani-khedira-lehnte-anfrage-aus-tunesien-ab_51559|publisher=Fussball Transfers|language=German|date=10 February 2015|accessdate=26 June 2017}}</ref>

In January 2026, Tunisia head coach [[Sabri Lamouchi]] and his assistant [[Michael Hefele]] traveled to Germany to renew discussions with Khedira regarding a potential switch of international allegiance ahead of the [[2026 FIFA World Cup]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Im neuen Jahr noch ohne Sieg – eine trügerische Situation für Union Berlin |url=https://www.kicker.de/im-neuen-jahr-noch-ohne-sieg-eine-truegerische-situation-fuer-union-berlin-1189470/artikel |publisher=Kicker |language=German |date=February 2026 |access-date=4 February 2026}}</ref> In February 2026, it was reported that he had agreed in principle to join the Tunisian national team, with negotiations described as progressing positively.<ref>{{cite news |title=Tunesien wirbt erneut um Union-Star Khedira |url=https://www.bild.de/sport/fussball/union-berlin-tunesien-wirbt-um-union-star-fuer-die-wm-2026-698094d178c88161f9da47ad |publisher=Bild |language=German |date=January 2026 |access-date=4 February 2026}}</ref> On 4 March 2026, Khedira's request to switch international allegiance to Tunisia was approved by [[FIFA]].<ref name="FIFA-CAP">{{cite news |url=https://knowledge.fifa.com/change-of-association-platform |title=FIFA Change of Association Platform |website=knowledge.fifa.com |date=4 March 2026|access-date=4 March 2026}}</ref>

==Personal life==
Khedira was born in [[Stuttgart]] to a German mother and a Tunisian father.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://kurier.at/sportundmotor/fussball/1916483.php |title=Deutsche Talente und ihre Alternativen |language=German |publisher=Kurier |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090619082146/http://kurier.at/sportundmotor/fussball/1916483.php |archivedate=19 June 2009 }}</ref> He is the younger brother of retired [[Germany national football team|Germany]] international [[Sami Khedira]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.kicker.de/khedira-und-der-vfb_rani-eifert-sami-nach-567352/artikel|title=Stuttgart: Auf den Spuren des großen Bruders Khedira und der VfB: Rani eifert Sami nach|publisher=[[Kicker Online]]}}</ref> He also has an older brother, Denny.<ref name="Khedira Stuttgart">{{cite web|url=http://www.vfb.de/de/vfb/aktuell/news-archiv/2013/296677--mein-verein-/|title="Mein Verein"|publisher=VfB Stuttgart|language=German|date=12 December 2013|accessdate=26 June 2017|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170626191037/http://www.vfb.de/de/vfb/aktuell/news-archiv/2013/296677--mein-verein-/|archivedate=26 June 2017|url-status=live}}</ref>

Khedira revealed that his father and older brother, Sami, influenced him to play football.<ref name="Khedira Stuttgart"/> He quoted on his position: ''"The Six is my primary position, but I've played as a centre-back, too, or have moved half a position forward when we're two-a-side, I think I can adapt anywhere."''<ref name="Khedira Stuttgart2"/> In response to being Sami's younger brother, Rani Khedira made it clear that he was not like his brother and that he wanted to go his own way.<ref>{{cite news|title=Neben SamiRani träumt von der Khedira-Doppelsechs|url=http://www.bild.de/sport/fussball/rani-khedira/traeumt-von-der-doppel-sechs-mit-sami-33812324.bild.html|publisher=Bild.de|language=German|date=11 December 2013|accessdate=26 June 2017}}</ref> Khedira also revealed that he has a qualification as a sports and fitness salesman.<ref>{{cite news|title=Der kleine Khedira erobert die Bundesliga|url=http://www.bild.de/sport/fussball/rani-khedira/der-kleine-khedira-erobert-die-liga-32584818.bild.html|publisher=Bild.de|language=German|date=27 September 2013|accessdate=27 June 2017}}</ref>

